gomodel:SYNGO_639  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Purified synaptic vesicles from a crude hippocampal LS1 fraction were analyzed using immunogold electron microscopy and western blotting to identify the localization of VGLUT2.\nFor figure 4a, synaptic vesicles were double stained for VGLUT2 and VGAT (arrow heads; large gold particles). The image clearly shows VGLUT2-labelled SVs. No KO control, secondary antibody alone did not produce a signal.\nin Figure 4b the LS1 fraction was analyzed using western blotting. A clear signal for VGLUT2 was observed in the total crude vesicular fraction, indicating that a subset of SVs in the fraction is expressing VGLUT2. In a sub-fraction of these SVs that was enriched for VGAT expression using immunoisolation, no signal for VGLUT2 was seen, which could be used as an indication for the specificity of the anti-VGLUT2 antibody.. Experimental description: Wistar rats, kept at the animal facilities at the Institute of Basic Medical Sciences, University of Oslo (Norway) or at VU University Medical Center (Amsterdam, The Netherlands), were handled according to the European regulations and under veterinary agreement and supervision." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_639" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

